There are a number of different fields in a JSON data structure.

The *name* is the name that will be used on the title.
The *order* is the order relevant to the structuring of the program.
The *time* just lists how long the lessons will take.
The *helpRoom* is the specific help room for this info.
The *isComingSoon* is either true or could be deleted.


```{markdown}
{
  "name": "Data Munging",
  "order": 2,
  "time": "0 hours",
  "helpRoom": "Help",
  "isComingSoon": true,
  "challenges": [
    {
      "id": "bd7128d8c441eddfbeb5bdd3",
      "title": "Data Munging",
      "description": [],
      "challengeSeed": [],
      "tests": [],
      "type": "Waypoint",
      "challengeType": 7
    }
  ]
}
```

The *challenges* and *type* is a bit more complex.  Before getting into the overall structure of each challenge, there are a number of
different challenge types. The challenge types are as follows.

Basic PPT style analysis is similar to type 7 and will be commonly used.
Type 2 is al

  html: 0, 'challenges/showHTML', (Not relevant)
  js: 1,   'challenges/showJS',   (Not relevant)
  video: 2,
  zipline: 3,    'challenges/showZiplineOrBasejump',  Enter a published notebook.
  basejump: 4,   'challenges/showZiplineOrBasejump',
  bonfire: 5, This is a javascript based analysis that won't be relevant.
  hikes: 6, This is a simple list of information followed by a quiz.
  **step: 7,**
  waypoint: 0



Challenge Type 7 is the first type, were just a click will get you through.  If you add a link, they have to click on the link.  There is a photo or a slide used to generate.


  4: 'challenges/showZiplineOrBasejump',
  This has a link to a video. A variety of steps and takes as an entry a
  github repository and a url.  Not sure what the URL would do.

  5: 'challenges/showBonfire',
         (This seems to be some javascript)
**  7: 'challenges/showStep'
        (0) Image file
        (1) Text description of the image
        (2) Content to be distplayed
        (3) Link to continue...sometimes they have to click link to continue. (Optional)
        (4) Credit to this person (Optional)
        (5) Link will be opened in a new window. Required if (4).


  6: Simple list of information

